{
  "text": "Remark 3. According to [CITATION_1] , the inverse of a cyclically banded positive definite matrix, such as PG S for banded GS, contains entries that decay exponentially (in absolute value) away from the diagonal and corners of the matrix, invoking a 'perturbation' on L \u2020 C .",
